## üß™ Option 4: NetSupport RAT *Behavior* Simulation

### üìÑ `netsupport_behavior_sim.txt`

```powershell
# ==============================
# SAFE RAT BEHAVIOR SIMULATION
# ==============================
# Simulates persistence + execution
# NO backdoor functionality

$runKey = "HKCU:\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run"
Set-ItemProperty -Path $runKey -Name "SimulatedRAT" -Value "powershell.exe -File fake.ps1"

Write-Output "[SIMULATION] Persistence key created (test only)"
```

‚úîÔ∏è Triggers:

* Registry modification
* Persistence detection
* SOC alerts

